From 81e781cdebd3d99480a150d19bf91b9812a1b81a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 19:14:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: password reset and email verification screens
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Neither existed at all despite the backend already supporting both flows
(forgot-password/reset-password/verify-email/resend-verification), so there
was no way for a user to actually recover a forgotten password or verify
their email from the app.

- ForgotPasswordScreen: two-step flow matching the backend's actual DTO
  shape (email -> forgot-password, then email + 6-digit code + new password
  -> reset-password). Reachable from a new "Mot de passe oublié ?" link on
  the login form.
- VerifyEmailScreen: shown right after registration completes, since the
  backend signs the user in immediately even though the account starts
  unverified. Code entry + resend, with a "plus tard" skip since
  verification isn't required to use the app.
- api_client.dart: added the four corresponding methods. Note the backend
  DTOs use email + a 6-digit code, not a token link — matched exactly.
- login_screen.dart: surfaces the actual backend error message on login
  failure instead of always showing "wrong password" — relevant now that
  the backend can also reject a login for a suspended/banned account with
  its own message, which was previously indistinguishable from a typo.
